race.comment: HEFFERNAN BALE (5) turned spotting a big start finishing fifth (24.33) last time in a Grade 4 at this track. Form at the trip sound including seven wins. Has ability and is a key runner. TUSKEN RAIDER (7) was impressive last time, posting an effortless 3.5 lengths win in taking a P5 in 24.04 and a new Best time this course and distance. Has the ability and looks a key chance. SIRIUS TODD (3) slotted in just off the lead from the wide draw last start and boxed on to finish second (23.78) at this track in a Grade 4/5 over 407m. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Expected to feature. VALIDATED (8) can play a role in the finish without surprising.
